If the rollback function is turned on, the rollback counter is initiated to rollbackInitCounterValue and decremented at each node restart occurred during the time rollbackInitTimerValue. When the time rollbackInitTimerValue has elapsed, rollback counter is reset to its initial value. If the rollback counter reaches the value 0 before the time rollbackInitTimerValue has elapsed, a rollback is made.

If the rollback function is turned on, the rollback timer is used to set the time limit during which node restarts decrement the rollbackCounter. The rollbackInitTimerValue starts from initial value after every node restart. After the given time, the node is not in a cyclic restart mode. The rollback counter, rollbackCounter, is then reset to its initial value.

If true, the system automatically updates the rollback counter at every node restart. A rollback is issued after x number of node restarts (Operated Initiated/Escalated), where x is defined by the rollbackInitCounterValue.
